Prompt Dependencies:
- types_TypeScript.prompt — provides `Annotation`, `CreateAnnotationInput`
- lib_db_TypeScript.prompt — provides `getDb()`

Instructions
- Generate a UUID for the annotation ID (`crypto.randomUUID()`).
- Store `drawingDataUrl` and `compositeDataUrl` as TEXT columns in the DB (base64 data URLs).
- `analysis_json` column starts as NULL (analysis is populated later via the `/[id]/analyze` endpoint).
- `resolved` column defaults to 0 (false).
- For POST: validate required fields (`sectionId`, `text`) and return 400 if missing.
- For GET: deserialize `analysis_json` → `analysis` for each annotation when reading from DB.

Deliverable
- `app/api/annotations/route.ts` — POST (create) and GET (list) handlers for annotations.

Note: The following endpoints are in SEPARATE route files (not in this file):
- `GET /api/annotations/[id]` → `app/api/annotations/[id]/route.ts`
- `POST /api/annotations/[id]/analyze` → `app/api/annotations/[id]/analyze/route.ts`
- `POST /api/sections/[id]/resolve-batch` → `app/api/sections/[id]/resolve-batch/route.ts`

Implementation assumptions (explicit)
- The DB `annotations` table has columns: `id`, `section_id`, `timestamp`, `text`, `video_file`, `drawing_data_url`, `composite_data_url`, `analysis_json`, `resolved`, `resolve_job_id`, `created_at`.
- No file system writes are needed in this route — data URLs are stored directly in the DB.

Please produce production-ready TypeScript code consistent with the above.
